<div id="c3">
<p>The beauty of Sci Foo is the blend of chance and democracy.  It is true Brownian motion of thoughtful people picked by the organizers.  It seems the meeting is intended to force unscheduled or unintended meetings and associations by people. The Organizers have been careful to select participants &#8212; we should trust them.</p>

<p>By labeling everybody with their affiliations &#8212; Harvard this, or Microsoft that &#8212; you introduce an unnecessary filter.  The corporates will go to their sessions and the academics will flock together, etc.  There are lots of meetings like that.</p>

<p>I doubt every book Aaron has read was a masterpiece but I hope that every book he has read was instructive in some way and perhaps in an unexpected way.</p>

